<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by Kioras on 11-22-2000 11:50 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Actually, I have sat on the outside of this whole debate on Everquest, and the rising 'demands' of the game.

I am currently running a Celeron 300, that is overclocked to 374, 192meg of ram, and an ATI Rage Fury Video card.  I have not had any trouble with the patch, or after it.  I have a friend running on 128meg of ram, and a P233, with a TNT 2 vid card, and he still runs fine.

In actuallity, the requirements to play Everquest are rather light, even now.  If you wish to play in Kunark, you need a much stronger machine then an original Pentium, and the adjustable graphical settings do leave a lot of 'wiggle room'.  As far as letting people play both the older version, and the current version, that would make things almost unplayable, due to the lag, and the extra resources required by verant.  (They would need about 50% or more power to run 2 pieces of software concurrently, not to mention having them access the same files and whatnot, can create bugged characters, crosslinked files, and other nightmares.)  They are barely able to keep up with the growth of Everquest through additional subscribers, and new servers.

If you weant to keep your ability to play Everquest, you have several low cost options.

If you have a P2, get a celeron 300-450 or so, for about $50-100.  Upgrade to 128 meg ram, or get a new graphics card.  (Stay away from the Voodoo's, they are not really the best price/performance out there)

If you have an original Pentium, and we know you are out there, you can either get a new computer(if you have $500 or so lying around, and a computer expert who can help you build it), or get a used computer, from the classifieds.  For about 150-200 you can find a used, but still useful(and powerful enough) P2 system, that can carry the weight needed for Everquest, until the next 'big' upgrade (probably in a year or so)

I'd rather put up with the 'step-by-step' upgrades of everquest, then have them write it off as a defunct game, making an Everquest 2, and letting us rot in the garbage pile.

Kioras</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
